@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Page not found";
    ViewData["BodyClass"] = "library-page";
}

@*
    Shared 404 view. Reached two ways:
      1. Status-code re-execute (Program.cs UseStatusCodePagesWithReExecute)
         — any unhandled 404 from any controller / static-file miss lands here.
      2. Direct return from controllers that detect a missing entity at the
         start of an action (e.g. AnimeController.Detail when the cross-
         service mapping has no record for the requested id).
    Mirrors the styling cues from the legacy inline "Anime not found"
    block: page-header headline, muted explainer, two CTAs side-by-side.
*@
<div class="page-header" style="text-align: center;">
    <h1 class="page-title">Page not found</h1>
    <p class="page-subtitle">The page you're looking for doesn't exist, or the content is no longer available.</p>
</div>
<div class="hero-ctas" style="justify-content: center;">
    <a class="hero-cta hero-cta-primary" href="/discover">Browse anime</a>
    <a class="hero-cta hero-cta-secondary" href="/">Dashboard</a>
</div>
